# QA Repository Structure Rules

## Overview
Defines repository structure rules for QA test case management with Jira/Xray.

## Repository Structure

### Top-Level Structure
```
jira-qa-space/
├── .cursor/
│   └── rules/                    # Cursor rules
├── utilities/
│   ├── jira-mcp-server/          # MCP server
│   └── README.md
├── test-plans/
│   └── [Project-Key]/            # Test plans by project
├── templates/                     # File templates
├── .gitignore
├── README.md
└── package.json
```

### Test Plans Structure
```
test-plans/
└── [Project-Key]/
    ├── [Project-Key].md          # Project overview
    └── [Epic-Key]/
        ├── [Epic-Key].md         # Epic test suite
        └── [Story-Key]/
            ├── [Story-Key].md    # Story test suite
            └── test-cases/
                └── [TC] *.md     # Individual test cases
```

### Example Structure
```
test-plans/
└── PROJ/
    ├── PROJ.md
    └── PROJ-100/
        ├── PROJ-100.md
        ├── PROJ-101/
        │   ├── PROJ-101.md
        │   └── test-cases/
        │       ├── [TC] PROJ-101 - Login - Verify Valid Credentials.md
        │       ├── [TC] PROJ-101 - Login - Verify Invalid Password.md
        │       └── [TC] PROJ-101 - Login - Prerequisites - Setup.md
        └── PROJ-102/
            ├── PROJ-102.md
            └── test-cases/
                └── [TC] PROJ-102 - Registration - Verify Success.md
```

## Folder Naming Conventions

### Project Level
- **Name**: Project Key (e.g., `PROJ`)
- **Content**: Project overview and settings

### Epic Level
- **Name**: Epic Issue Key (e.g., `PROJ-100`)
- **Content**: Epic description and test suite overview

### Story Level
- **Name**: Story Issue Key (e.g., `PROJ-101`)
- **Content**: Story test suite

### Test Cases Level
- **Folder Name**: Always `test-cases`
- **Content**: Individual test case files

## File Naming Conventions

### Project File
```
[Project-Key].md
Example: PROJ.md
```

### Epic/Story File
```
[Issue-Key].md
Example: PROJ-100.md, PROJ-101.md
```

### Test Case File
```
[TC] [Issue-Key] - [Feature] - [Test Name].md
Example: [TC] PROJ-101 - Login - Verify Valid Credentials.md
```

### Prerequisites File
```
[TC] [Issue-Key] - [Feature] - Prerequisites - Setup.md
Example: [TC] PROJ-101 - Login - Prerequisites - Setup.md
```

## Automatic Structure Creation

### From User Story URL
Use MCP tool `jira_get_story_hierarchy(issueKey)` to get `projectKey`, `epicKey`, `storyKey`, and `folderPath`. Create the folder structure using the returned `folderPath`. Epic is taken from Jira `parent` field; if no parent, `epicKey` equals `storyKey` (fallback path: `test-plans/PROJ/STORY/test-cases/`).

## File Templates Location

### Templates Directory
```
templates/
├── test-case-template.md
├── test-suite-template.md
├── test-plan-template.md
└── prerequisites-template.md
```

### Template Usage
- Copy template when creating new file
- Replace placeholders with actual values
- Follow template structure

## Quick Reference

### Common Commands
```bash
# Create project structure
mkdir -p "test-plans/PROJ"

# Create epic structure
mkdir -p "test-plans/PROJ/PROJ-100"

# Create story structure with test-cases
mkdir -p "test-plans/PROJ/PROJ-100/PROJ-101/test-cases"
```

### Finding Files
```bash
# Find all test cases for a story
ls "test-plans/PROJ/PROJ-100/PROJ-101/test-cases/"

# Find all test suites
find test-plans -name "*.md" -not -path "*/test-cases/*"

# Find all test cases
find test-plans -path "*/test-cases/*.md"
```

## Hierarchy Mapping

| Jira Level | Repository Level | File Type |
|------------|-----------------|-----------|
| Project | `test-plans/[KEY]/` | [KEY].md |
| Epic | `test-plans/[PROJ]/[EPIC]/` | [EPIC].md |
| Story | `test-plans/[PROJ]/[EPIC]/[STORY]/` | [STORY].md |
| Test Case | `test-plans/.../test-cases/` | [TC] *.md |

## Special Files

### .gitkeep
Place in empty directories to preserve structure:
```
test-plans/.gitkeep
```

### Index Files
Each level can have an index file:
```
test-plans/PROJ/PROJ.md           # Project index
test-plans/PROJ/PROJ-100/PROJ-100.md  # Epic index
```

## Migration Notes

### From Azure DevOps Structure
If migrating from Azure DevOps qa-space:
- Replace Work Item IDs with Jira Issue Keys
- Update URL formats
- Adjust field mappings
